  // WindShared — shared inputs
  std_ec1w_tip_terrain: 'The terrain category describes the roughness of the upwind terrain. Categories 0–IV range from open sea (0) to urban areas with tall buildings (IV). It affects z_0, z_min, and the roughness factor c_r. See EN 1991-1-4 §4.3.2 and Annex A.',
  std_ec1w_tip_vb: 'The basic wind velocity v_b = v_b,0 · c_dir · c_season, where v_b,0 is the fundamental value defined in the National Annex. The directional and season factors are generally 1.0. See EN 1991-1-4 §4.2(1)P.',
  std_ec1w_tip_c0: 'The orography factor c_0 accounts for speed-up effects over isolated hills and escarpments. For flat terrain c_0 = 1.0. Values greater than 1.0 may apply at hilltops — see EN 1991-1-4 §4.3.3 and Annex A §A.3.',
  std_ec1w_tip_rho: 'Air density used to compute dynamic pressure. The default value is 1.25 kg/m³ per EN 1991-1-4 §4.5(1). It may be adjusted for altitude or temperature per the National Annex.',
  // WindFreewall
  std_ec1w_tip_fw_l: 'Total length of the freestanding wall. Used in the aspect ratio l/h and characteristic length e = min(l, 2h). Longer walls transition through zones A, B, C, D along their length.',
