  std_ec1w_tip_ws_ecc: 'The resultant wind force acts at eccentricity e = ±(e/b) · b from the geometric centre, creating a torsional moment T_w = ±(e/b) · b · F_w. The standard default is e/b = 0.25. Both +e and −e cases must be checked. See EN 1991-1-4 §7.4.3.',
